id: pmc-ry1j
title: Post-release production readiness continuation audit
description: "Continuation pass requested on 2026-05-23 to re-verify pm-changelog production readiness after npm publication, including release gates, temp-folder pm install behavior, GitHub state, changelog self-generation, npm installability, and final commit/push state."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[3]: governance,release,verification
created_at: "2026-05-23T20:05:46.615Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T20:17:55.922Z"
deadline: "2026-05-23T00:00:00.000Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "- npm run release:check passes from the repository checkout.\\n- Clean temp folder verifies pm install npm:pm-changelog --project and pm changelog generate.\\n- GitHub repository and release metadata are verified with gh using free features only.\\n- npm registry exposes the current package version and package contents are installable.\\n- pm health and strict validation pass after this continuation audit is documented.\\n- Any intentional changelog or pm governance changes are committed and pushed."
reviewer: steve
risk: medium
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: v2026.05.23
resolution: "Completed date-based production release v2026.05.23 with npm-compatible package version 2026.5.23, deterministic pm-release grouped changelog generation, passing release gates, strict pm validation, public npm publication, public GitHub release, and clean temp-folder pm install verification."
expected_result: "pm-changelog remains production-ready, public, installable via pm install npm:pm-changelog --project, and governed by valid pm records."
actual_result: "All checked release gates passed under package version 2026.5.23; npm exposes 2026.5.23 as latest; GitHub release v2026.05.23 is public and latest; clean temp project /tmp/pm-changelog-date-lTmdf1 installed npm:pm-changelog, generated a changelog containing Verify date release npm install, package doctor returned ok=true with zero warnings, and the installed extension version is 2026.5.23."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pmc-ysps,related,"2026-05-23T20:05:46.615Z",codex,null
comments[12]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T20:05:46.615Z",codex,Continuation audit started after pm validate showed the previous release hierarchy is closed and healthy.
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,"GitHub evidence: gh release view v0.1.0 reports tag v0.1.0, published 2026-05-23T19:35:03Z, non-draft and non-prerelease. gh repo view reports PUBLIC visibility, main default branch, Issues enabled, Wiki and Projects disabled, README homepage, and release-related topics."
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,"npm evidence: npm view pm-changelog reports version=0.1.0, dist-tags.latest=0.1.0, license=MIT, repository=git+https://github.com/unbraind/pm-changelog.git."
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,"Release gate evidence: npm run release:check passed on 2026-05-23 with TypeScript check, 16 node:test tests, production npm audit with 0 vulnerabilities, npm pack dry-run producing 25 files, and changelog:check reporting CHANGELOG.md up to date."
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,"Temp install evidence: clean project /tmp/pm-changelog-prod-fPCquv ran pm init, pm install npm:pm-changelog --project, created and closed a smoke item, generated CHANGELOG.md with item_count=1, rg found Verify production npm install, and pm package doctor returned ok=true with zero warnings."
  "2026-05-23T20:08:57.696Z",codex,"Release scope update: because the continuation audit added a new committed changelog/governance artifact after v0.1.0, the final public release target is promoted to patch version 0.1.1 so npm and GitHub releases match repository HEAD."
  "2026-05-23T20:14:52.148Z",codex,"Release scope corrected per maintainer direction: pm-changelog now follows pm CLI date-based release versioning. npm metadata uses SemVer-compatible 2026.5.23, while GitHub tag/release naming uses v2026.05.23."
  "2026-05-23T20:15:54.488Z",codex,"Changelog script update: npm run changelog and npm run changelog:check now use --group-by release with replace mode so CHANGELOG.md is rebuilt deterministically from pm release metadata, including v2026.05.23."
  "2026-05-23T20:15:54.488Z",codex,"Package metadata update: package.json, package-lock.json, and manifest.json now use npm-compatible date version 2026.5.23. The public GitHub tag/release target is v2026.05.23."
  "2026-05-23T20:17:55.914Z",codex,"Final GitHub evidence: git tag v2026.05.23 was pushed to origin with main, and gh release create published https://github.com/unbraind/pm-changelog/releases/tag/v2026.05.23 as the latest release."
  "2026-05-23T20:17:55.914Z",codex,"Final npm-source install evidence: clean project /tmp/pm-changelog-date-lTmdf1 ran pm init, pm install npm:pm-changelog --project, generated CHANGELOG.md with item_count=1 for Verify date release npm install, pm package doctor returned ok=true with zero warnings, and installed extension package.json reported version 2026.5.23."
  "2026-05-23T20:17:55.914Z",codex,"Final publication evidence: npm publish completed for pm-changelog@2026.5.23 using a temporary npm config, npm view reports latest=2026.5.23, and npm registry lists versions 0.1.0 and 2026.5.23."
notes[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T20:05:46.615Z",codex,This pass should not reopen prior release items; it records fresh evidence against the already-published package.
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,An earlier temp harness at /tmp/pm-changelog-prod-fOTUwq failed because it used an unsupported pm create flag and guessed an internal managed package path; the corrected set -e smoke at /tmp/pm-changelog-prod-fPCquv is the accepted verification evidence.
  "2026-05-23T20:08:57.696Z",codex,The 0.1.1 patch release contains release governance and changelog evidence only; runtime package code is unchanged from the verified 0.1.0 build.
  "2026-05-23T20:14:52.148Z",codex,"Npm package versions cannot include a leading v or zero-padded numeric components, so package.json uses 2026.5.23 and the public Git tag/release uses v2026.05.23."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T20:05:46.615Z",codex,A separate continuation chore keeps post-publication verification auditable without altering the original release epic closure evidence.
  "2026-05-23T20:07:12.268Z",codex,"For npm-source pm package verification, use the installed extension command and pm package doctor instead of relying on a guessed managed node_modules path."
